<item>
            <title>[LU-18081] conf-sanity test_98: Buffer overflow check failed</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18081</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b46be262-bd73-4a2e-b1e1-bab749185dbe&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b46be262-bd73-4a2e-b1e1-bab749185dbe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_98 failed with the following error on Ubuntu 24.04 and SLES15sp6:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Buffer overflow check failed
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b_es6_0/681&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b_es6_0/681&lt;/a&gt; - 6.8.0-31-generic&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b_es6_0/681&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b_es6_0/681&lt;/a&gt; - 3.10.0-1160.102.1.el7_lustre.ddn17.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like newer kernels have changed the way that mount arguments are being processed, so this subtest is now &quot;failing&quot; because the mount is not rejecting the long mount option.  It may be related to what &quot;mount&quot; is printing for the error message, or it may be that it is handling the mount options differently and they are not triggering an error when they are only &lt;tt&gt;PAGE_SIZE+8&lt;/tt&gt; bytes long.&lt;/p&gt;







&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
conf-sanity test_98 - Buffer overflow check failed&lt;/p&gt;</description>
